        "name": "Synthesis of prior pedicle screw FEA validation studies",
        "description": "A comprehensive synthesis aggregating findings from twelve independent FEA validation studies of spinal instrumentation published between 2008 and 2022. The synthesis integrates material property characterisation data, contact algorithm benchmarks, and boundary condition sensitivity analyses from FDA-commissioned studies, peer-reviewed journal articles (Spine, Journal of Biomechanics, Medical Engineering & Physics), and OEM internal reports. Collectively, these sources establish the baseline modelling assumptions — elastic moduli for Ti-6Al-4V rod and screw body, frictional coefficient at the rod-tulip interface, and cortical bone surrogate stiffness — that underpin the COU1 ensemble model. The narrative weight of this node in the credibility argument is substantial: without it, the acceptance of material and contact parameter choices would rest solely on the primary bench comparison, which tested only a single loading configuration."
